      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "> Does this need to be reported as a bug?\r\n\r\nDefinitely, yes.\r\n\r\n> When a software is installed to the `Program Files` / `Program Files (x86)` folder, the setup program is always run with administrator rights. This means that the installation program is allowed to change permission settings for a folder.\r\n\r\nBitcoin installer has to ask for admin rights when launched, or at least when `%ProgramFiles%` is selected as destination folder for the installation. And if it is installed to Program Files, then it has to change folder permission to allow writing files there.\r\n\r\nSetup tools may allow adding a script line to handle that. Found [this](http://www.samlogic.net/blog/2013/08/how-to-give-a-standard-user-write-permission-to-a-folder-in-program-files/) blog article that may be interesting.",
      "created_at" : "2017-11-13T11:37:54Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/11668#issuecomment-343893725",
      "id" : 343893725,
      "issue_url" : "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/11668",
      "updated_at" : "2017-11-13T11:37:54Z",
